This paper deals with distributed computing models and the complexity of computing and approximating functions and predicates with limited computational power. The paper specifically focuses on population protocols, which fall under the category of distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with information theory and communication complexity, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper discusses the efficiency of computation, which is relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
